			<div class="content" id="post-content-1137842">
									

<p>I don't have a good Ancient Evil Thing in mind right now, unfortunately. But it really IS the central concept of this SCP &#8212; the facility was built to contain it, it's still there, and it's about to escape. I really want to be scared of it&#8230;</p>
<p>Plot hole: If containing The Thing in Room 166 is the point of the facility, why was the Agent able to just open a door and walk in on the thing? Or conversely, why didn't the Thing open the door and get out years ago? It feels like some interesting containment method is missing there.</p>

