				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adam-smascher" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(587467); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=587467&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182896" alt="Adam Smascher" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=587467)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adam-smascher" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(587467); return false;" >Adam Smascher</a></span> <span class="odate time_1303957901 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Apr 2011 02:31</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1138161">
									

<blockquote>
<p>SCP-557 is an underground bunker constructed almost entirely of sandstone and mud bricks&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>The foundation of SCP-557, as well as all of its exterior and some interior walls, are comprised of sandstone bricks roughly 23 m3. Interior partitions have been constructed in some of the larget chambers, primarily of mud brick&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>More than a bit redundant.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>So far over █████ such remains have been found, leading researchers to believe that SCP-557 was intended and used as a military complex. This hypothesis is supported by the presence of what appear to be defensive features, <strong>although the actual function of these features is uncertain</strong>, as some seem to <strong>face inward</strong> instead of outward.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The Foundation is not that dense. If I can figure this out, so can they. There's a difference between implications arising from things left unsaid and painting the Foundation as idiots in order to avoid making statements of the obvious.</p>
<p>There's a lot of information given that I'm not sure we need. The details about the elevator, for example. Just say there are anomalous devices/mechanisms/whatever, give a few examples, and we'll get the idea.</p>

							</div>

								
					
